--
-- Description: 16X32 number font lookup table. Version meant for presenting
--              the numbers 0..9 and a space for small applications.
--              The use of this font limits the amount of used FLASH memory.
--
-- Sources: Font created by Mike.
--
-- Notes: The character numbering does NOT follow the ASCII table numbering 
--        so you need to add 32 (0x20) to the character to be written. 
--        See lib glcd_font.jal for font explanation.
--

-- Font ID, unique amongst font libs.
